data.name: MainGuidedReading1
data.value: After our children develop a solid phonics foundation we encourage them to move on to our Guided Reading courses. These courses are based off of the US Common Core learning Standards, which means your child will do more than read words from a page. They will be asked critical thinking questions during each reading course designed to create interest in the reading material. All of the critical thinking questions stem from the 5 W's. Who, What, Where, When, Why? During these courses your child can expect to be exposed to an abundance of genre's including Fiction, Non-Fiction, Animal-Fantasy, Folk-Tales, Encyclopedia Entries and much much more.

data.name: MainGuidedReading2
data.value: Read more about our Guided Reading programs here.

data.name: MainLearningOutcomes1
data.value: It's no longer sufficient to pay a large amount of money for your child to 'learn' English and at the end of the day have nothing to show for it. Our trademarked technology allows you, the parent, to be constantly updated on your child's progress so there are no surprises when examination time comes. Recent studies have shown that only 30% of education comes from the educational environment. The other 70% comes from their home life and their time spent with their friends. At the end of each class you will receive a notification, via our in-house engineered android / iOS mobile app, or an email that shows what exactly your child learned that day as well as some simple excercises you can do at home to help re-inforce your child's learning.

data.name: MainPhonicsFirst1
data.value: Phonics are the building blocks of learning English. Starting with memorizing each letter in fun and engaging ways. Then we work on digraphs - combining letters to make very common sounds in the english language. From there we work on what we call CVC words, or Consonant-Vowel-Consonant words like dog, cat, mom, dad, etc. Eventually we move on to the more intricate sections of the English language including the "Silent E" words that end wit the letter E but the letter itself isn't spoken. Trigraphs, homonyms, synonyms and antonyms follow as you near the end of your phonics journey. We have taken great care to prioritize these skills for ease, utility, and fun!

data.name: MainPhonicsFirst2
